#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-vtkHDFWriter.md:1
msgid "Support writing VTKHDF files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-vtkHDFWriter.md:3
msgid ""
"Previously, only reading VTKHDF files from VTK was supported. We introduce "
"`vtkHDFWriter`, capable of writing sequentially VTK data structures to disk "
"in the VTKHDF format. So far, the writer is capable of writing static and "
"time-dependent data for vtkPolyData, vtkUnstructuredGrid and their "
"vtkPartitionedDataset versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-vtkHDFWriter.md:8
msgid ""
"vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection and vtkMultiBlockDataSet are also supported, "
"without temporal support. These composite types have the option to be "
"written either in a single standalone file, or as a collection of files: one "
"describing the composite assembly structure, and every other containing the "
"data relative to a non-composite leaf. Both are considered equivalent by the "
"reader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-vtkHDFWriter.md:14
msgid ""
"Temporal datasets and vtkPartitionedDataset can also be written in separate "
"files, one for each time step or partition, with a main file that references "
"their data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-vtkHDFWriter.md:17
msgid ""
"Distributed writing is supported for distributed data with pieces written by "
"different processes in individual files, and grouped as a partitioned "
"dataset by the rank 0 using virtual datasets when pieces are poly data or "
"unstructured grid. Temporal data and static meshes are also supported in "
"distributed writing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-vtkHDFWriter.md:21
msgid ""
"User can compress chunked dataset thanks to the CompressionLevel option."
msgstr ""
